tomes.com/content/view/14/69/ |title=Wildside/Owlswick ''Necronomicon'' |date=2006-12-19 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603131414/http://www.mythostomes.com/content/view/14/69/ |archive-date=June 3, 2008 |access-date=March 3, 2007}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikisource|History of the Necronomicon|History of the ''Necronomicon''}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100828075757/http://www.reocities.com/clorebeast/necpage.htm \"The Dan Clore ''Necronomicon'' Page\"], Everything You Never Wanted to Know about the ''Necronomicon'' (''Al Azif'') of the Mad Arab Abdul Alhazred but Weren't Afraid Enough to Know Better than to Ask!\n* Low, Colin. [http://www.digital-brilliance.com/necron/necron.htm \"The ''Necronomicon'' Anti-FAQ\"] (September 1995)\n* {{librivox book | title=The King in Yellow | author=Robert W. CHAMBERS}}\n* {{librivox book | title=Vathek | author=William BECKFORD}}\n* {{librivox book | title=The Nameless City | author=H. P. Lovecraft}}\n* {{librivox book | title=The Dunwich Horror | author=H. P. LOVECRAFT}}\n\n{{H.P. Lovecraft|state=collapsed}}\n\n<!-- \"Category:Fictional books\" IS ALREADY A PARENT OF THE CATEGORY BELOW-->\n<!-- \"Category:Fictional grimoires\" IS ALREADY A PARENT OF THE CATEGORY BELOW-->\n[[Category:Fictional books within the Cthulhu Mythos]]\n\n[[Category:Demonological literature]]\n[[Category:Fictional elements introduced in 1922]]\n", "name_user": "Red dwarf", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Necronomicon"}
{"title_page": "Ala-Too International University", "text_new": "{{coord|42|51|21.6|N|74|40|52.4|E|display=title}}\n{{Infobox university\n |name              = Ala-Too International University\n |native_name       = \u041c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442 \u00ab\u0410\u043b\u0430-\u0422\u043e\u043e\u00bb\n |image_name        = Ala-Too International University Seal.png\n |image_size        =\n |caption           = \n |latin_name        =\n |former_name       = Ala-too International University\n |motto             =\n |mottoeng          =\n |established       = 1996\n |closed            =\n |type              =\n |affiliation       =\n |endowment         =\n |officer_in_charge =\n |chairman          =\n |chancellor        =\n |president         =\n |vice-president    =\n |superintendent    =\n |provost           =\n |vice_chancellor   =\n |principal         =\n |dean              =\n |director          =\n |head_label        =\n |head              =\n |faculty           =\n |staff             =\n |students          =\n |undergrad         =\n |postgrad          =\n |doctoral          =\n |other             =\n |address           = 1/8 Ankara Street\n |city              = [[Bishkek]]\n |province          = [[Chuy Province]]\n |country           = [[Kyrgyzstan]]\n |coor              =\n |campus            =\n |former_names      =\n |free_label        =\n |free              =\n |sports            =\n |colors            =\n |colours           =\n |nickname          =\n |mascot            =\n |athletics         =\n |affiliations      =\n |website           = {{url|www.iaau.edu.kg}}\n |logo              =\n |footnotes         =\n}}\nThe '''Ala-Too International University'''  ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442 \u00ab\u0410\u043b\u0430-\u0422\u043e\u043e\u00bb}}; {{lang-tr|Uluslararas\u0131 Ala-Too \u00dcniversitesi}}), formerly known as the '''International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University''', is a private university located in [[Bishkek]], [[Kyrgyzstan]]. It was established in 1996. The university offers graduate, master's, and doctoral programs. It is often ranked as one of Kyrgyzstan's most prestigious universities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thediplomat.com/2016/07/turkish-targeting-of-gulen-movement-reaches-into-central-asia/|title=Turkish targeting of G\u00fclen movement reaches into Central Asia|last=Putz|first=Catherine|date=25 July 2016|website=The Diplomat|access-date=14 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[English language|English]] is the primary [[medium of instruction]] at the university. However, some classes are taught in [[Russian language|Russian]] and a few other classes are taught in [[Turkish language|Turkish]].\n\nThe Ala-Too International University is funded and run by the global Islamic education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/turkey-gulen-movement-global-aim/27872225.html|title=In wake of blown coup, Turkey takes global aim at Gulen Movement|last=Recknagel|first=Charles|date=21 July 2016|website=Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|access-date=14 November 2017}}</ref> Following the [[2016 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat attempt]], which the Turkish government blames on G\u00fclen, the university changed its name from the International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University to the Ala-Too International University, appointed a Kyrgyz rector, and generally started to position itself more as a local institution.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Building B of IAAU.jpg|thumb|The Ala-Too International University was known as the International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University until 2016]]\nThe Ala-Too International University was established as the International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University in 1996 by the Sebat Educational Foundation which promotes and follows the tenets of Islam espoused by [[Fethullah G\u00fclen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/world/asia-pacific/erdogan-seeks-to-close-kyrgyz-schools-and-colleges-linked-to-exiled-cleric-1.2746767|title=Erdogan seeks to close Kyrgyz schools and colleges linked to exiled cleric|last=Starr|first=Stephen|date=5 August 2016|website=The Irish Times|access-date=14 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn the wake of the [[2016 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat attempt]], which the Turkish government blames on G\u00fclen, the administration of Turkish president [[Recep Tayyip Erdo\u011fan]] demanded that Kyrgyzstan close down institutions affiliated with the [[G\u00fclen movement]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://24.kg/obschestvo/60117_bolee_11tyisyach_kyirgyizskih_uchaschihsya_nepustyat_vturtsiyu/|script-title=ru:\u0411\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0435 11 \u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447 \u043a\u044b\u0440\u0433\u044b\u0437\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0443\u0447\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0445\u0441\u044f \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0443\u0441\u0442\u044f\u0442 \u0432 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0446\u0438\u044e|trans-title=More than 11,000 Kyrgyz students will not be allowed to enter Turkey|last=Bengard|first=Anastasiya|date=14 August 2017|website=24|access-date=14 November 2017|language=Russian}}</ref> However, the Kyrgyz government refused to comply with Ankara's demands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://24.kg/obschestvo/60197_kakoy_privet_chinovniki_otreagirovali_nazayavlenie_turetskih_kolleg_osebate/|script-title=ru:\u041a\u0430\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0442... \u0427\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0430\u0433\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u044f\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0442\u0443\u0440\u0435\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u043b\u043b\u0435\u0433 \u043e \u00ab\u0421\u0435\u0431\u0430\u0442\u0435\u00bb|trans-title=As you salute... Officials react to the statement of Turkish colleagues on Sebat|date=15 August 2017|website=24|access-date=15 November 2017|language=Russian}}</ref>  In February 2017, the Turkish government announced that diplomas issued by the Ala-Too International University would no longer be valid in Turkey.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ilyasov|first1=Rustem|script-title=ru:\u0414\u0438\u043f\u043b\u043e\u043c\u044b \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442\u0430 \"\u0410\u0442\u0430\u0442\u044e\u0440\u043a-\u0410\u043b\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043e\" \u0431\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u0435 \u043d\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0446\u0438\u0438|trans-title=Diplomas of Ataturk Ala-Too University no longer accepted in Turkey|url=https://kloop.kg/blog/2017/02/04/diplomy-universiteta-atatyurk-alatoo-bolshe-ne-prinimayutsya-v-turtsii/|accessdate=1 February 2018|work=Kloop|date=4 February 2017|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nSubsequently, the name of the university was changed from the International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University to the Ala-Too International University. The name of the organization that runs the Ala-Too International University along with 35 other schools and colleges was also changed from the Sebat Educational Foundation to the Sapat Educational Foundation. (''Sapat'' means quality in [[Kyrgyz language|Kyrgyz]].)\n\n== Academics ==\nThe Ala-Too International University has the following departments and programs:\n\n=== Faculty of New Technologies ===\n*  Computer science\n*  Electronics and nanoelectronics engineering\n*  Applied mathematics and IT\n\n=== Faculty of Social Sciences ===\n[[File:Main campus of IAAU.JPG|thumb|Main campus of the Ala-Too International University]]\n*  Turkology\n*  \u0421hineese language and translation\n*  Simultaneous translation\n*  English language and literature\n*  Pedagogy\n*  Psychology\n*  Journalism\n\n=== Faculty of Economics and Administrative Sciences ===\n*  World economy and international business\n*  International relations\n*  Management\n*  Finance and banking\n*  Law\n*  Accounting and audit\n*  Industrial engineering\n\n=== Faculty of Medicine ===\n[[File:IAAU Graduates, Class of 2011.JPG|thumb|right|Ala-Too International University graduation ceremony, Class of 2011]]\n*  General medicine\n*  Pediatrics\n\n=== Vocational Education ===\n*  Economy and accounting\n*  Banking\n*  Marketing\n*  Computer systems and complexes\n*  Software engineering\n*  Design\n*  Jurisprudence\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.iaau.edu.kg/ Official website] {{in lang|en|ru|ky}}\n*[http://www.alatoo.edu.kg/ Official website] {{in lang|en|ru|ky}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ala-Too International University}}\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1996]]\n[[Category:Universities in Kyrgyzstan]]\n", "text_old": "{{coord|42|51|21.6|N|74|40|52.4|E|display=title}}\n{{Infobox university\n |name              = Ala-Too International University\n |native_name       = \u041c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442 \u00ab\u0410\u043b\u0430-\u0422\u043e\u043e\u00bb\n |image_name        = Ala-Too International University Seal.png\n |image_size        =\n |caption           = \n |latin_name        =\n |former_name       = International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University\n |motto             =\n |mottoeng          =\n |established       = 1996\n |closed            =\n |type              =\n |affiliation       =\n |endowment         =\n |officer_in_charge =\n |chairman          =\n |chancellor        =\n |president         =\n |vice-president    =\n |superintendent    =\n |provost           =\n |vice_chancellor   =\n |principal         =\n |dean              =\n |director          =\n |head_label        =\n |head              =\n |faculty           =\n |staff             =\n |students          =\n |undergrad         =\n |postgrad          =\n |doctoral          =\n |other             =\n |address           = 1/8 Ankara Street\n |city              = [[Bishkek]]\n |province          = [[Chuy Province]]\n |country           = [[Kyrgyzstan]]\n |coor              =\n |campus            =\n |former_names      =\n |free_label        =\n |free              =\n |sports            =\n |colors            =\n |colours           =\n |nickname          =\n |mascot            =\n |athletics         =\n |affiliations      =\n |website           = {{url|www.iaau.edu.kg}}\n |logo              =\n |footnotes         =\n}}\nThe '''Ala-Too International University'''  ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0435\u0436\u0434\u0443\u043d\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442 \u00ab\u0410\u043b\u0430-\u0422\u043e\u043e\u00bb}}; {{lang-tr|Uluslararas\u0131 Ala-Too \u00dcniversitesi}}), formerly known as the '''International Atat\u00fcrk-Alatoo University''', is a private university located in [[Bishkek]], [[Kyrgyzstan]]. It was established in 1996. The university offers graduate, master's, and doctoral programs. It is often ranked as one of Kyrgyzstan's most prestigious universities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thediplomat.com/2016/07/turkish-targeting-of-gulen-movement-reaches-into-central-asia/|title=Turkish targeting of G\u00fclen movement reaches into Central Asia|last=Putz|first=Catherine|date=25 July 2016|website=The Diplomat|access-date=14 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[English language|English]] is the primary [[medium of instruction]] at the university. However, some classes are taught in [[Russian language|Russian]] and a few other classes are taught in [[Turkish language|Turkish]].\n\nThe Ala-Too International University is funded and run by the global Islamic education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/turkey-gulen-movement-global-aim/27872225.html|title=In wake of blown coup, Turkey takes global aim at Gulen Movement|last=Recknagel|first=Charles|date=21 July 2016|website=Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty|access-date=14 November 2017}}</