ones Parliament]].<br /> The following were nominated for The Four Northern Counties collectively: <br/>Major-General [[Charles Howard, 1st Earl of Carlisle|Charles Howard]], Robert Fenwick, [[Henry Dawson (MP)|Henry Dawson]], [[Henry Ogle]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[First Protectorate Parliament|1654]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Colonel [[William Briscoe (politician)|William Briscoe]]  ||rowspan=\"3\"|<!-- party -->\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Major-General [[Charles Howard, 1st Earl of Carlisle|Charles Howard]]||rowspan=\"2\"|\n|-\n|[[Second Protectorate Parliament|1656]]\n|-\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Third Protectorate Parliament|January 1659]]\n|[[Sir Wilfrid Lawson, 1st Baronet, of Isell|Sir Wilfrid Lawson]] ||<!-- party -->\n|-\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|[[Rump Parliament|May 1659]]\n|colspan=\"6\"|''Not represented in the restored [[Rump Parliament|Rump]], Airmine having died in the interim''\n|-\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" | || style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|April 1660\n|[[Sir Wilfrid Lawson, 1st Baronet, of Isell|Sir Wilfrid Lawson]] ||\n|[[Charles Howard, 1st Earl of Carlisle|Charles Howard]] ||\n|-\n|style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" | || style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" rowspan=\"2\" |\n|1661\n|[[Patricius Curwen|Sir Patricius Curwen, Bt]] ||\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Sir George Fletcher, 2nd Baronet|Sir George Fletcher, Bt]] || rowspan=\"2\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" rowspan=\"6\"|\n|1665\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Sir John Lowther, 2nd Baronet|Sir John Lowther, Bt]] || rowspan=\"6\"|\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|February 1679\n|[[Richard Lamplugh]] ||\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{/meta/color}}\" |\n|August 1679\n|[[Edward Howard, 2nd Earl of Carlisle|Viscount Morpeth]] ||\n|-\n|